# MealMates-Ionic Project Overview

## Project Description
MealMates is an Ionic/Angular recipe discovery and management app with Firebase backend and SQLite local storage. The app uses standalone components and follows modern Angular patterns.

## Key Technologies
- **Frontend**: Ionic 8+ with Angular 19+ standalone components
- **Backend**: Firebase Auth, Firestore, Storage
- **Local Storage**: SQLite via @capacitor-community/sqlite
- **Build System**: Capacitor for native builds
- **PWA**: Progressive Web App with [manifest.json](mdc:src/manifest.json)

## Project Structure
- **Main Config**: [angular.json](mdc:angular.json), [capacitor.config.ts](mdc:capacitor.config.ts)
- **Firebase**: [firebase.config.ts](mdc:firebase.config.ts), [firebase.json](mdc:firebase.json)
- **Routes**: [src/app/app.routes.ts](mdc:src/app/app.routes.ts)
- **Services**: `src/app/services/` - Auth, SQLite, Recipe services
- **Pages**: `src/app/pages/` - All page components
- **Models**: `src/models/` - TypeScript interfaces
- **Assets**: `src/assets/` - Icons, images, static files

## Key Features
- User authentication with Firebase Auth
- Recipe browsing and management
- Favorites stored locally with SQLite
- Tab-based navigation
- Profile management
- Recipe creation with image upload
- PWA capabilities

